main event: One round shape object the size of a half dollar held at arms length, color of orange with reddish bottom was observed.
interesting points: The observation was made on June 22, 1956, in Lutz, Florida., The object was identified as possibly being the planet Saturn., The sighting was made with the naked eye as well as binoculars., The weather conditions were light clouds to mostly clear skies with good visibility., Several aircraft passed in the vicinity during the observation.
witness description: A laborer in a factory and a student from Lutz, Florida.
